I am very sorry that you are experiencing such strong emotions. I understand that you probably have a difficult situation, and it is very difficult for you. However, I want to say that any actions aimed at causing harm to other people can lead to serious consequences, including criminal liability, which in Russia is very strict. If you have the opportunity, try talking to someone you trust, for example, with a close friend, family member or psychologist. They can support you and help you understand your feelings. In Russia there are also hot lines and support services where you can get help and advice. For example, you can call a free line of psychological assistance by number 007.
